cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with 3D object reconstruction from multiple viewpoints. It may also belong to the Graphics (cs.GR) sub-category as it involves rendering and geometric reasoning. The use of deep learning techniques for generative modeling suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the optimization aspect of the proposed framework suggests that it could also belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
